  - Set the continuation bit (0x80) on all chunks except the last one.
  - Append to the result vector.
- For `from_bytes`:
  - Iterate over bytes.
  - Accumulate 7-bit chunks into a `u32`.
  - If a byte has MSB set, continue accumulating.
  - If MSB is clear, finalize the number and push to result.
  - If we reach the end of bytes while MSB was set on the last byte, it's an `Error::IncompleteNumber`.
  - Also, check for overflow? The problem says "restrict ourselves to only numbers that fit in a 32-bit unsigned integer." VLQ encoding of a 32-bit number can take up to 5 bytes. We should handle potential
overflow during decoding if necessary, but the instructions don't explicitly mention it. Usually, in this exercise, overflow isn't tested or we can just assume valid input or return an error. I'll stick to
